<br>
We are going to brainstorm a response to Bruce Gagnon's article at Spacedaily. Not only to contents in the article but all your favourite Gnaw n' Pis quotes from past stories. Michio Kaku, Karl Grossman and others from the opposition ranks are going to do their best to scare the devil out of the public. Think of gutter science you have heard them state in the past and dig it up if you can. I'll put together an article from our pooled data and submit it to Spacedaily for publication. The great nuclear space debate has finally begun. We've waited years for this opportunity to present our case. Let's not allow the luddites to win this time around. They helped to murder past efforts to nuclearise space and our generations suffered for it. Let's help give the next generation a chance to enjoy wider horizons and a greater standard of living. Humanity needs it's dreams. We will never reach the Stars if we can't first tame our own backyard. The solar system cannot be conquered without nuclear power. There is never just cause to prohibit the peaceful application of technology. That path leads nowhere but to a new dark age.<br>
<br>
The battle for helms deep is at an end but the war for middle earth is only.....sorry, wrong movie. Bruce Gagnon isn't Sauron. Just a misguided fool who thinks we would all be happier living in caves.<br>
<br>
I'll start putting material together at NSMedia. I have an idea how to start it. We will have to appeal to people's sense of adventure, patriotism and hopes. Logic alone won't sway people. We have to give them a reason to want this new direction. Telling them why we can do it only opens them up to the possibility. We have to also tell them why we should do it. Gagnon mentions a Mars Mission. Obviously he has bought all the hype. Much of the public has too. While we can't state that a Mars Mission is definite we can address Gagnons reference to it and maybe stir the publics imagination a little.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/27/03 9:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: NuclearSpace Vs Global Network.</span><hr size=1> A few ideas:<br>
