an class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: NuclearSpace Vs Global Network.</span><hr size=1> joe, pat, carrol, and a few others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 776<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/29/03 8:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: NuclearSpace Vs Global Network.</span><hr size=1> Is Michio Kaku Japanese?  I know that a lot of Japanese names for females often end in 'O' but maybe Michio is one of those names that can be used for either sex the way &quot;Kelly&quot; can be in English.  Anyhow, engineers usually understand how to apply science better than scientists themselves do.  I wouldn't trust an airplane that was designed by a theoretical physicist for instance.  I'd feel much safer in one that was designed by an aerospace engineer.  Like wise, I believe Zubrin has more experience and probably deeper knowledge of how spacecraft power systems work than does Kaku who only knows the theoretical basics.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1911<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/30/03 12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclea